
              cards - Package Management Utilities for NuTyX
              based on the development of the tool pkgutils

               http://www.fukt.bth.se/~per/pkgutils/


Description
-----------
cards is a set of utilities (xxx-add, xxx-rm, xxx-info, xxx-mk and xxx-rejmerge),
which are used for managing software packages in Linux. It was originally developed for
and used by the CRUX distribution (http://crux.nu). This is a fork of this work for the 
NuTyX distribution including the handling of the binaries


Building and installing
-----------------------
 1. To build the libs

$ make all
$ make libs

 2. To build the binaries

$ make

 3. To install the binaries / the libs

$ make install
or
$ make DESTDIR=/some/other/path install


Converting the database
-----------------------

To make shure cards find the information about the packages, it's necessary to convert the DB

$ pkginfo -c

